{
  "title": "Pause and buffer",
  "slug": "pause-and-buffer",
  "publishedAt": "2019-05-10T05:43:00.000Z",
  "excerpt": "Many times when we have a conversation with someone, we’re so focused on what we’re going to say next that we forget to focus on listening to what’s being said.",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "1 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Many times when we have a conversation with someone, we’re so focused on what we’re going to say next that we forget to focus on listening to what’s being said.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Yet wouldn’t it be better to simply say what comes to mind? Free, spontaneous, unassuming, thought?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What if you defaulted to using a buffer instead?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "A go-to phrase, perhaps, so you have ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "something",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "  to say, but not enough that it takes your mind off of listening to the person doing the talking.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "In no particular order, here are some things you might say instead:",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "really(?)",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "certainly",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "true",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "right",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "absolutely",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "seriously?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "is that right?",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "exactly!",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "definitely",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "yeah",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "\n",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "gotcha",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "See? That’s not too difficult. (And it’s easy to remember a few).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "All it is is a way to simply say, “that’s interesting” or “I’m listening” or “tell me more,” and in doing so, enabling you to ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "listen",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "as opposed to thinking about what to next say.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It turns out that taking your mind off mindlessly talking (and thinking about talking) is a great way to get back to listening intently, and saying something impactful, instead.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
